Definition.WordDefinition: nonmusical adj 1: lacking interest in or talent for music; "too unmusical to care for concerts"; "it is unfortunate that her children were all nonmusical" [syn: {unmusical}] [ant: {musical}] 2: not musical in nature; "the unmusical cry of the bluejay" [syn: {unmusical}, {dissonant}] [ant: {musical}]
